04479nam a22006375i 9780292795594DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20212006txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927955947 a10.7560/7147242doi  a(DE-B1597)587715  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 4aPC2271b.B76 2006eb 7aFOR0000002bisacsh04a448.2/4212221 aBrodsky, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aFrench Verbs Made Simple(r) /cDavid Brodsky. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©2006  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tPART I. FORMS OF VERBS -- t1. Present Tense -- t2. Imperfect Tense and Present Participle -- t3. Past Participle -- t4. Simple Past (Passé Simple) -- t5. Future and Conditional Tenses -- t6. Subjunctive and Imperative -- t7. Compound Verb Forms -- t8. Orthographic Modifications -- t9. Summary -- tPART II. USES OF VERBS -- t10. Indicative -- t11. Present and Past Subjunctive -- t12. Simple Past and Imperfect Subjunctive -- tPART III. ANNEXES -- tA. Model Verbs, with Complete Conjugations -- tB. Alphabetical Listing of 6,200 Verbs by Model Number -- tC. Defective Verbs -- tSelected References0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIt's time for a new approach to learning French verbs. Unlike popular verb guides that require the rote memorization of hundreds of verb forms, this book clearly explains the rules that govern the conjugation of all classes of French verbs—especially the irregular ones that give second-language learners the most trouble. These straightforward, easy-to-understand rules for conjugating French verbs are effective learning tools for both beginning students and more advanced speakers who want to perfect their usage of French verb forms. French Verbs Made Simple(r) has many helpful features that you won't find in any other verb guide: Clear explanations of all verb tenses and forms. The simple patterns and rules that govern the conjugation of all verbs—including those verbs whose irregularities follow patterns that can be easily learned. A detailed discussion of how each verb form is used, with numerous examples. A full explanation of whether a verb should be conjugated with avoir or être, and the conditions under which the past participle is variable—two of the thorniest problems for students of French. An extended treatment of the subjunctive that will help you understand why it is used in some situations but not others. Complete conjugations for 57 basic model verbs (along with 27 "variants") and a comprehensive listing of some 6,200 verbs that indicates which of the models each verb follows. Going well beyond any other guide in the clarity and detail of its explanations—as well as the innovative manner in which individual verbs are linked to model conjugations—French Verbs Made Simple(r) is the only guide to French verbs a learner needs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFrench languagevTextbooks for foreign speakersxEnglish. 0aFrench languagexVerb. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / General.2bisacsh  aFrench Language, French translation, verbs, learning.40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/71472440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292795594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292795594/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK